values.label: LoR
values.rules:
**Objective: Complete "The Law of Retribution."**
http://content.warframe.com/dynamic/trialStats.php

Completion Notes: 
[Phase 1] Destroy all 4 injectors. 
[Phase 2] You must complete the puzzle with a success by stepping on the same amount of pads as the number of players that started the raid, then move the core to the exit. 
[Phase 3] Blow up all 5 areas to Vay Hek, then drop his HP to 0 to trigger the ending.

Forbidden:
* ~~Walking through the bottom two doors in Stage 1 without using the buttons.~~
* Portaling through the doors in Stage 2 before they are opened normally.

values.label: LoRNM
values.rules:
**Objective: Complete "Nightmare: The Law of Retribution."**
http://content.warframe.com/dynamic/trialNightmareStats.php

Completion Notes: 
[Phase 1] Destroy all 4 injectors. 
[Phase 2] You must complete the puzzle with a success by stepping on the same amount of pads as the number of players that started the raid, then move the core to the exit. 
[Phase 3] Blow up all 5 areas to Vay Hek, then drop his HP to 0 to trigger the ending.

Forbidden:
* ~~Walking through the bottom two doors in Stage 1 without using the buttons.~~
* Portaling through the doors in Stage 2 before they are opened normally.

values.label: JV
values.rules:
**Objective: Complete "Jordas Verdict."**
http://content.warframe.com/dynamic/trialGolemStats.php 

Completion Notes: 
[Phase 1] You need to break all walls, then complete the decryption sequence to 100%. 
[Phase 2] You must get through the first door and push the elevator to the top. 
[Phase 3] You must destroy all 3 nerves and kill Jordas.

Forbidden:
* Using the exhaust vents in Stage 2 to reach the console faster.
**Completion note:** 100% completion is dictated by successfully hacking and recovering all data from all three vaults using any method.

values.label: U10 Bosses No Items
values.rules:
Defeat the following bosses in any order:
- Captain Vor (Mercury)
- Jackal
- Nef Anyo
- Sargus Ruk
- Alad V (Jupiter)
- Tyl Regor
- Hyena Pack
- Ambulas
- Lech Kril
- Kela De Thaym
- Raptor
- Vor+Kril (Phobos)
- Lephantis

Time starts when starting the timer (clicking "Play Now") for the first mission and ends when seeing the "Mission Complete" screen at the end of the last mission. Items NOT allowed (except those such as Scanners, Trappers, etc.) - items may be equipped as long as they are not used. Warframe build swaps allowed. No Platinum usage during the run. Single-segment only. To avoid any possible item usage with partners, this category is Solo only.

** Keep in mind that exploits that could be easily patched out should not be used in runs. They aren't banned, but if patched out they could make runs invalid.
** Please submit times WITH loads.

values.label: U19 Bosses
values.rules:
Defeat all fixed-encounter bosses in the game in any order. Time begins upon starting the countdown of the first assassination mission and ends when the mission complete screen appears for the last mission. 

The following bosses must be defeated: 
- Captain Vor 
- The Jackal 
- Vay Hek 
- Lech Kril 
- The Sergeant 
- Lech Kril & Captain Vor (on Ceres) 
- Alad V 
- Raptors 
- Sargus Ruk 
- Tyl Regor 
- Hyena Pack 
- Ambulas 
- Jordas Golem 
- Mutalist Alad V 
- Kela de Thaym 
- Lephantis 
- Phorid 

Rules are as follows: 
- All Warframe/weapons/gear items are available to use. 
- You may not run missions in parallel for Co-op runs. 
- Final time must include loads to the nearest second. 
- Single segment only. 
- Platinum usage is forbidden. 
- Beacons are forbidden. 
- Must be glitchless. 
- Field and raid bosses are not included in this run. 

This is a seasonal category and any updates to the bosses will result in these runs becoming Legacy as U19 Bosses.

level_categories.name: Co-op
level_categories.rules:
* Co-op runs must begin and end with the same players.
* All players must extract. Usage of the spectator state after bleeding out to skip going to extraction is not allowed.
* You may not run missions in parallel for Co-op runs.
* Any intentional disconnects/crashes will invalidate your submission.
* Runs must be recorded from host perspective or a screenshot of Mission Success from the host must be provided in the description.
